oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Minute book and corresponding notes
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Minute book of the John Ingram Bivouac, including rules of order, a check to Daniel W. Emmett by the organization for their appreciation to the author of "Dixie," and various notes including "The Colored Brothers Song" and a list of veterans' deaths. John Ingram was a Confederate soldier in the 6th Tenn. Inf. Regt., CSA. The John B. Ingram Bivouac, Camp 5 was a group of Confederate veterans from Jackson, Madison County, Tennessee.
